name: Lamball
lore: A walk up a hill tends to end with this Pal tumbling back down. This causes it to become dizzy and unable to move, making it easy to capture and kill. As a result, this Pal has tumbled down to the very bottom of the food chain itself.
title: Big Floof

partnerSkill.name: Fluffy Shield
partnerSkill.description: When activated, equips to the player and becomes a shield. Sometimes drops wool when assigned to a Ranch.

name: Cattiva
lore: At a glance it appears confident, but it is in fact weak and cowardly. Being toyed with by Cattiva is in many ways the greatest of disgraces.
title: The Cat's Pajamas

partnerSkill.name: Cat Helper
partnerSkill.description: While in a team, Cattiva helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.

name: Chikipi
lore: Extremely weak and far too delicious. It is one of the weakest Pals alongside Lamball. No matter how many are hunted, they just keep appearing.
title: Plump & Juicy

partnerSkill.name: Egg Layer
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes lays an egg when assigned to Ranch.

name: Lifmunk
lore: Intelligent as a five to seven-year-old human child. It makes a wonderful partner, but there have been more then a few cases where they've killed their master after learning to use weapons.
title: Coward of the Steppe

partnerSkill.name: Lifmunk Recoil
partnerSkill.description: When activated, leaps onto the player's head and uses a submachine gun to follow up player attacks.

name: Foxparks
lore: It is unskilled at controlling fire from the moment it is born and tends to choke on the flames it breathes unintentionally. Foxparks sneezes are one of the leading causes of forest fires.
title: Revealer of Paths

partnerSkill.name: Huggy Fire
partnerSkill.description: When activated, equips the player and transforms into a flamethrower.

name: Fuack
lore: Using its own body water, this pal can create waves anywhere. its body surfs when in a hurry, but the resulting speed often ends in a fatal collision.
title: Rowdy Wave Ripper

partnerSkill.name: Surfing Slam
partnerSkill.description: When activated, Fuack body surfs toward an enemy and slams into them.

name: Sparkit
lore: It is always on edge during the dry season. Sparks can fly with even the slightest provocation, even amongst allies.
title: Livewire Tabby

partnerSkill.name: Static Electricity
partnerSkill.description: While in a team, increases the attack power of Electric Pals.

name: Tanzee
lore: Long ago, this Pal used long objects like tree branches as weapons. After coming into contact with humans, however, it found something much more effective: guns.
title: Dexterous Primate

partnerSkill.name: Cheery Rifle
partnerSkill.description: When activated, Tanzee will mercilessly fire an assault rifle at nearby enemies.

name: Rooby
lore: Wild Rooby surprisingly never get sick. Eating one piece of charcoal a day, made by burning a branch, is the secret to its eternal health.
title: Chief of the Herd

partnerSkill.name: Tiny Spark
partnerSkill.description:
While in a team, increases attack power of 
Fire
 Pals.

name: Pengullet
lore: Its wings have degraded substantially, and it cannot fly. Yet it has lingering sentiment for the skies in its DNA, and sometimes tries to fly again.
title: Ate Too Much

partnerSkill.name: Pengullet Cannnon
partnerSkill.description: When activated, the player equips a Rocket Launcher and fires Pengullet as ammunition. Pengullet explodes on contact and is incapacitated.

name: Penking
lore: Surprisingly, it is unrelated to Pengullet. Ever wanting attention, this Pal will strut its stuff for any onlookers.
title: Pioneer of the Frozen Sea

partnerSkill.name: Brave Sailor
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, Fire Pals drop more items when defeated.

name: Jolthog
lore: It releases the electricity stored in its body when under attack, producing a shock that can be over 10 million volts. If thrown, it can be more lethal then any conventional heavy weaponry.
title: Don't Touch!

partnerSkill.name: Biribiri Bombs
partnerSkill.description: When activated, equips Jolthog to the player's hand. When thrown at an enemy, causes an electric explosion upon impact.

name: Jolthog Cryst
lore: It releases the cold air stored in its body when under attack. The frigid blast it radiates is cold enough to freeze the surrounding air and easily pierces through any attacker's body.
title: Watch Your Feet!

partnerSkill.name: Cold Bomb
partnerSkill.description: When activated, equips Jolthog Cryst to the player's hand. When thrown at an enemy, causes an icy explosion upon impact.

name: Gumoss
lore: A strange pal with a body resembling tree sap. It gradually loses strength if it has nothing to cover its body with, eventually rotting away.
title: Suddenly Transformed

partnerSkill.name: Logging Assistance
partnerSkill.description: While in a team, improves efficiency of cutting trees.

name: Vixy
lore: The idol of Palpagos Islands. If you bully a Vixy, you best be prepared to become enemies with the whole world.
title: Star of the Steppe

partnerSkill.name: Dig Here!
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes digs up items from the ground when assigned to a Ranch.

name: Hoocrates
lore: Often lost in thought, it sometimes finds it difficult to sleep. "I think, therefore I am."
title: Purveyor of Wisdom

partnerSkill.name: Dark Knowledge
partnerSkill.description: While in a team, increases attack power of Dark Pals.

name: Teafant
lore: Large amounts of water pour from what is thought to be its nose, though some say that it is, in fact, just snot. This has sparked a fierce debate among Pal scholars.
title: Adorable Watering Can

partnerSkill.name: Soothing Shower
partnerSkill.description: When activated, spouts mysterious water that soothes wounds and restores the player's HP.

name: Depresso
lore: It has few friends because of the perpetually grouchy look on its face, but it is in fact kindhearted. Some have seen it feeding Vixy who have strayed from their pack.
title: Several Sleepless Nights Later

partnerSkill.name: Caffeine Inoculation
partnerSkill.description: When activated, Depresso chugs a bunch of energy drinks, drastically increasing its movement speed for a certain time.

name: Cremis
lore: Compared to Lamball, it has finer wool and a temperament more suited for domestication. However, it has historically always been kept as a pet. Cuteness is considered a virtue.
title: Darling Furball

partnerSkill.name: Fluffy Wool
partnerSkill.description: While in a team, increases attack power of Neutral Pals. Sometimes drops Wool when assigned to a Ranch.

name: Daedream
lore: It puts those it is interested in to sleep and shows them an endless stream of happy dreams. Those who fall under its spell are never to wake until death takes them.
title: Dream Eater

partnerSkill.name: Dream Chaser
partnerSkill.description: While in a team, appears near the player. Follows up player attacks with magic bullets.

name: Rushoar
lore: Being an extremely aggressive Pal, it often picks fights before gauging its opponent's strength. Though small, its powerful charge can even send boulders flying.
title: Woodland Ruffian

partnerSkill.name: Hard Head
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Increases efficiency of destroying boulders while mounted.

name: Nox
lore: If you find Nox hair in your bedding, you should leave it where it lays and leave immediately. Picking it up is a one-way ticket to a never ending night.
title: Dusken Aristocrat

partnerSkill.name: Kuudere
partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, applies Dark damage to the player's attacks.

name: Fuddler
lore: Its large claws boast diamond-like hardness. However, sharpening these claws consumes most of its energy, leading it to sometimes spend entire days doing nothing else.
title: Underground Explorer

partnerSkill.name: Ore Detector
partnerSkill.description: When activated, generates subtle variations to detect nearby ore.

name: Killamari
lore: It wraps itself around an enemy's head, sucking out their insides. Pal mummies are occasionally found, but these are in fact Killamari victims.
title: Emotionless

partnerSkill.name: Fried Squid
partnerSkill.description: While in a team, it can be summoned and used as a glider. It can float for long periods of time while gliding.

name: Mau
lore: Its hard tail does not deteriorate even when cut off. Some believed these severed tails to be good luck but, for the innumerable Mau who where poached as a result, they where anything but.
title: Noble Glimmer

partnerSkill.name: Gold Digger
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes digs up Gold Coin when assigned to a Ranch.

name: Mau Cryst
lore: Its crystalline tail is beautiful, but shatters when this Pal dies. Some believe it is good luck to raise one, so Mau Cryst in captivity are treated with great care.
title: Serene Glimmer

partnerSkill.name: Gold Digger
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes digs up Gold Coin when assigned to a Ranch.

name: Celaray
lore: Riding the wind, this Pal travels where it pleases. Should it find a partner along the way, the encounter will mark its journey's end.

partnerSkill.name: Zephyr Glider
partnerSkill.description: While in a team, it can be summoned and used instead of a glider. Allows you to move quickly for long periods of time while gliding with this Pal.

name: Direhowl
lore: Long ago, Direhowl would hunt alongside humans. But over the years this bond faded.
title: Hunter of the Steppe

partnerSkill.name: Direhowl Rider
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Moves slightly faster than most mounts.

name: Tocotoco
lore: A frightening Pal that produces exploding eggs. It often fires these eggs from its rear end as a weapon, but when spent the Pal itself explodes.
title: Boom or Bust

partnerSkill.name: Eggbomb Launcher
partnerSkill.description: When activated, equips to the player and transforms into an egg launcher.

name: Flopie
lore: It prefers places that have an abundance of vegetation, but hay fever has apparently become a problem for Flopie as of late.

partnerSkill.name: Helper Bunny
partnerSkill.description: While in a team, appears nearby the player. Automatically picks up nearby items.

name: Mozzarina
lore: Milk pours from this Pal like water from an open faucet, regardless of its gender. It's truly a mystery of life, although this mystery may be better left unsolved.
title: Grade A Beef

partnerSkill.name: Milk Maker
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes produces Milk when assigned to a Ranch.

name: Bristla
lore: This prickly Pal's thorns are highly poisonous. It is friendly with Cinnamoth and only smiles when a Cinnamoth is drinking its nectar.
title: Thorny Rose

partnerSkill.name: Princess Gaze
partnerSkill.description: While in a team, increases attack power of Grass Pals.

name: Gobfin
lore: Long ago, it was a large and powerful aquatic Pal. As food become scarce, it evolved to live on land. Since walking requires much energy, it gradually became smaller and is now a small and puny Pal.
title: Sea Thug

partnerSkill.name: Angry Shark
partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Aqua Gun. While in a team, increases player's attack power.

name: Gobfin Ignis
lore: Once upon a time, it was a giant and powerful aquatic Pal. However, with the dwindling availability of food, it ventured onto land. As a consequence of burning many calories to walk, it astonishingly awakened its power to control fire!
title: Volcano Thug

partnerSkill.name: Angry Shark
partnerSkill.description: When activated, atacks targeted enemy with a powerful Spirit Fire. While in a team, increases player's attack power.

name: Hangyu
lore: Its strong arms can rip apart even iron. As a particularly cruel form of execution, serious criminals would be strung up in a public square, and a Hangyu would rip off the skin from their bones.
title: Bringer of Luck

partnerSkill.name: Flying Trapeze
partnerSkill.description: While in a team, can be summoned and used instead of a glider. Carries the player up high while gliding.

name: Hangyu Cryst
lore: Its gigantic arms can tear through blocks of ice. There were times when great sinners were tied in the town square and had their hair torn out by Hangyu Cryst as a brutal form of public humiliation.
title: Glacial Harbinger

partnerSkill.name: Winter Trapeze
partnerSkill.description: While in team, can be summoned and used instead of a glider. Carries the player up high while gliding.

name: Mossanda
lore: A Pal so powerful it's hard to believe. In one experiment, this pal tore through 3,000 pieces of paper at once! It's only by some miracle this Pal isn't a meat-eater.
title: Guardian of the Forest

partnerSkill.name: Grenadier Panda
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can rapidly fire a grenade launcher while mounted.

name: Mossanda Lux
lore: A Pal whose power is truly shocking. By altering the electrical currents in its body, this Pal has been able to overload its own strength. When it comes to sheer power, this Pal may be top of the list.
title: Inheritor of the Storm

partnerSkill.name: Grenadier Panda
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can rapidly fire a grenade launcher while mounted.

name: Woolipop
lore: Its entire body is 18,000 times sweeter then sugar.
title: Giant Cotton Candy

partnerSkill.name: Candy Pop
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes drop Cotton Candy when assigned to a Ranch.

name: Caprity
lore: The shrub on this Pal's back produces berries as long as it's properly fed. It offers these berries to potential mates, and if the flavor is to their liking, romance blossoms.

partnerSkill.name: Berry Picker
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes drops Red Berries from its back when assigned to a Ranch.

name: Melpaca
lore: Don't be fooled by its fluffy appearance. A hypersonic kick from one of its long legs may send you flying to the other side of the world.

partnerSkill.name: Pecapaca Wool
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Sometimes drop Wool when assigned to a Ranch.

name: Eikthyrdeer
lore: The one who possesses the most impressive antlers becomes the leader of the herd. If their antlers are broken, they become depressed and leave the herd, never to be seen again.
title: Protector of the Herd

partnerSkill.name: Guardian of the Forest
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can perform a double jump while mounted. Increases efficiency of cutting trees.

name: Eikthyrdeer Terra
lore: The individual with the hardest horns becomes the leader. once the horns are lost, so too is its leadership status. it leaves the herd amidst farewell glances and quickly returns to the earth.
title: Antlers of Gold

partnerSkill.name: Guardian of the Golden Forest
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Can perform a double jump while mounted. Increases efficiency of cutting trees.

name: Nitewing
lore: It carries newborn Pals to its nest and raises them as a surrogate parent. Once the baby Pal is of eating age, it hunts them.
title: Wings of the Firmament

partnerSkill.name: Travel Companion
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden as a flying mount.

name: Ribbuny
lore: A Pal who's never without a bright smile. Occasionally, it gets its tentacles tied up in knots by Cattiva's pranks. During those moments, its expression changes to something altogether demonic.
title: Heart-melting Smile

partnerSkill.name: Skilled Fingers
partnerSkill.description: While in team, increases attack power of Neutral Pals. While at a base increases efficiency if working at Weapon Workbench.

name: Incineram
lore: In the dark of night, this pal snatches pray to bring back to its territory. what happens to those poor souls afterwards isn't to hard to imagine.
title: Hyena of the Wild

partnerSkill.name: Flameclaw Hunter
partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Hellfire Claw.

name: Incineram Noct
lore: It specifically targets baby pals, taking them back to its territory. One can only imagine the profound despair of the parent Pal, whose child has been taken away.
title: Hyena of the Darkest Night

partnerSkill.name: Darkclaw Hunter
partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Swallow Kite.

name: Cinnamoth
lore: Sniffing its scales produces a feeling of unparalleled euphoria. There was some effort to further regulate this byproduct, but the Free Pal Alliance have vehemently opposed these measures, putting a stop to them.
title: Butterfly Promenade

partnerSkill.name: Mysterious Scales
partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with Poison Fog.

name: Arsox
lore: In ancient times, carnivorous Pals pursued them relentlessly. The absurd fury in the cries of Arsox transformed into a raging inferno, which has been passed on to this day.
title: Blazing Brute

partnerSkill.name: Warm Body
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Keeps the rider warm in cold environments.

name: Dumud
lore: When too relaxed, its reaction time drastically declines. Even if it were sliced from head to tail, it probably wouldn't even realize that it should be dead until the next morning.
title: Perpetual Procrastinator

partnerSkill.name: Soil Improver
partnerSkill.description:
While in team, increases attack power of 
Ground
 Pals.

name: Cawgnito
lore: Long ago it freely soared the skies. After losing a contest with Galeclaw, it abandoned the skies and now lives a quiet nocturnal life.
title: Shadow-cloaked Schemer

partnerSkill.name: Telepeck
partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Phantom Peck

name: Leezpunk
lore: A Pal that always takes great care to maintain a stylish stance. Always on the hunt for the coolest poses, if given a mirror it will spend all day posing in front of it.
title: Self-proclaimed Genius

partnerSkill.name: Sixth Sense
partnerSkill.description: When activated, utilizes a sixth sense to detect nearby dungeons.

name: Leezpunk Ignis
lore: A Pal that has an unusual obsession with their standing posture. Always in search of the hottest pose, this Pal's owner is constantly presented with fervent stances.
title: Self-proclaimed Fashionista

partnerSkill.name: Sixth Sense
partnerSkill.description: When activated, utilizes a sixth sense to detect nearby dungeons.

name: Loupmoon
lore: The horns on its head grow under the moonlight. It doesn't hate the sun, but its horns itch when sunlight hits them.
title: Enraptured by Moonlight

partnerSkill.name: Claws Glistening in the Dark
partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Jumping Claw.

name: Galeclaw
lore: A pal that can easily take flight even when grasping a human. it is, however, prone to letting go when tired, which has led to the sudden demise of more then a few souls.
title: Proud Courier

partnerSkill.name: Galeclaw Rider
partnerSkill.description: While in team, can be summoned and used instead of a glider. Allows you to fire a gun while gliding with this Pal.

name: Robinquill
lore: A pal that is very similar to humans who hunt and live in the forests. It may prove to be a key for understanding what Pals are and how they diverged from humans so long ago.
title: Archer of the Forest

partnerSkill.name: Hawk Eye
partnerSkill.description: When fighting together, increases damage player deals to enemy weak points.

name: Robinquill Terra
lore: A Pal that lives a hunting life in rocky areas and is very close to humans. When Robinquill Terra bones are found in ruins, there are always human bones found nearby as well.
title: Archer of the Sands

partnerSkill.name: Hawk Eye
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, allows you to deal more damage to weak points.

name: Gorirat
lore: It beats the ground rhythmically to communicate with its comrades. The meaning of each rhythm differs by troop, but the distinction between them is still largely unknown.
title: Jungle Punk

partnerSkill.name: Full-power Gorilla Mode
partnerSkill.description: When activated, unleashes a primal fury that increases Gorirat's attack power.

name: Beegarde
lore: A servant that pledges loyalty to Elizabee. Any that cause harm to the queen are immediately expelled from the hive. It will gladly give its life to protect its queen.
title: Guardian Commander

partnerSkill.name: Worker Bee
partnerSkill.description:
Sometimes drop Honey when assigned to Ranch.

While in team, Elizabee's stats will be increased.

name: Elizabee
lore: A chosen queen to rule over Beegardes. There is a never ending stream of servants willing to work themselves to death for the pleasure of serving their queen.
title: Empress of the Hive

partnerSkill.name: Queen Bee Command
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, stats will increase the more Beegarde are in your team.

name: Grintale
lore: Grintale's eyes light up the moment anyone enters its territory. This is no figure of speech-its eyes literally light up
title: Marshmallow Body

partnerSkill.name: Plump Body
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Enhances 
Neutral
 attacks while mounted.

name: Swee
lore: Crawling along the ground, it eats microscopic organic matter. After a while, it discharges any substances that provide no nutrition. By using it as a mop for cleaning, everyone wins!
title: Curious Floof

partnerSkill.name: Fluffy
partnerSkill.description: While in team, Sweepa's stats will be increased.

name: Sweepa
lore: While hibernating, a large number of Swee hide within its voluminous body hair. The most ever recorded is 101.
title: Majesty of Fuzz

partnerSkill.name: King of Fluff
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, stats will increase the more Swee are in your team.

name: Chillet
lore: It can curl its body and roll around at extremely highspeeds, long ago, people would tie bags of milk to domesticated Chillet as they grazed to produce butter using this spinning.

partnerSkill.name: Wriggling Weasel
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Applies 
Dragon
 damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

name: Univolt
lore: It used to be considered an emissary of the Thunder God, and thus was not hunted by people. However, after witnesses observed one die from a lightning strike, its reverence faded, and it quite literally fell into the role of a workhorse.
title: Swift Deity

partnerSkill.name: Swift Deity
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Applies 
Electric
 damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

name: Foxcicle
lore: On nights when the aurora is visible, it looks up towards the sky and begins to howl a beautiful song. This does, however, leave it vulnerable to attacks from enemies.
title: Claws of Ice

partnerSkill.name: Aurora Guide
partnerSkill.description:
While in a team, increases attack power of 
Ice
 pals.

name: Pyrin
lore: Its entire body has evolved into a highly efficient radiator, gifting it with astounding stamina. When someone has mounted it, this Pal takes caution not to burn them.
title: Steed of Flames

partnerSkill.name: Red Hare
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Applies 
Fire
 damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

name: Pyrin Noct
lore: It burns mysterious dark matter as energy and expels the remaining particles from its body. If someone rides it, they should take care so as not to gallop down the path of darkness.
title: Steed of Darkness

partnerSkill.name: Black Hare
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Applies Dark damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

name: Reindrix
lore: Its transparent cerulean antlers glow with the cold of absolute zero. Any who touch them with their bare hands are instantly frozen over and smashed to pieces.
title: Beast of Blizzards

partnerSkill.name: Cool Body
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Keeps the rider cool in hot environments.

name: Rayhound
lore: At full speed, it could be mistaken for a bolt of lightning. If two Rayhounds collide, the sound is like that of a powerful thunderclap.
title: Electro-charged Zoomies

partnerSkill.name: Jumping Force
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Can double jump while mounted.

name: Kitsun
lore: Despite its appearance, Kitsun is extremely sensitive and will flee to a cave when spooked. Long ago, it was considered an ill omen if one were found nearby.
title: Guardian of the Azure Flame

partnerSkill.name: Clear Mind
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden. Unaffected by the cold or heat while riding this Pal.

name: Dazzi
lore: often kind to lonely pals. however the moment a pal mistakes this for actual companionship it seizes the opportunity to blast them with a thunderbolt.
title: Born of the Storm

partnerSkill.name: Lady of Lightning
partnerSkill.description:
While in team, appears near the player.

Follows up the player attacks with lightning bolts.

name: Lunaris
lore: It can control those who carelessly stare into its eyes, those seen with a Lunaris are in its mind, simply under its control.
title: Extraterrestrial

partnerSkill.name: Antigravity
partnerSkill.description: While in team, Lunaris manipulates gravity, increasing the player's max carrying capacity.

name: Dinossom
lore: A pal who once angered cannot be pacified. it rages on and on like an inferno. the phrase "step on a Dinossom's tail" had come to mean enraging someone.
title: Guardian of Blossoming Gardens

partnerSkill.name: Fragrant Dragon
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Enhances 
Grass
 attacks while mounted.

name: Dinossom Lux
lore: Though struck by lightning, it lives on. the phrase "struck by a Dinossom Lux's bolt" has come to mean narrowly escaping death.
title: Guardian of Lightning

partnerSkill.name: Thunder Dragon
partnerSkill.description:
Enhances 
Electric
 attacks while mounted.

name: Surfent
lore: Its hydrodynamic form is well suited to life in water. Poachers often catch them and use them in place of surfboards.
title: The Ocean's Wrath

partnerSkill.name: Swiss Swimmer
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden to travel on water.

While mounted, prevents stamina depletion while moving over water.

name: Surfent Terra
lore: Its aerodynamic form is well suited to life on the sand. Poachers often catch them and use them in place of surfboards.
title: The Desert's Wrath

partnerSkill.name: Sand Swimmer
partnerSkill.description: Can be ridden.

name: Maraith
lore: It relishes the peculiar scent living things give off when they are near death. If a has taken a liking to you, it is safe to assume that is why.
title: Messenger of Death

partnerSkill.name: Messeger of Death
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden.

Applies 
Dark
 damage to the player's attacks while mounted.

name: Digtoise
lore: a walking contradiction, possessing the strongest shell and the only drill capable of piercing it "Digtoise's Fable" is a popular children's tale.
title: Drilling Machine

partnerSkill.name: Drill Crusher
partnerSkill.description: When activated, performs Shell Spin, follows the player while spinning, and mines ores efficiently.

name: Tombat
lore: Often appears out of the blue to flaunt its prized wings in front of other Pals. Although this appears to be an intimidation tactic, the Pal seems to derive some kind of pleasure from the display.
title: Trickster

partnerSkill.name: Ultrasonic Sensor
partnerSkill.description: When activated, uses ultrasonic waves to detect the location of nearby Pals.

name: Lovander
lore: Seeking a night of love, it is always chasing someone around. At first it only showed interest in other Pals, but in recent years even humans have become the target of its debauchery.
title: Pal on the Prowl

partnerSkill.name: Heart Drain
partnerSkill.description: While fighting together, grants the player and Lovander the life steal effect which absorbs some of the received damage and restores HP.

name: Flambelle
lore: When it starts crying, this Pal produces magma in place of tears. The magma that pours out is absorbed back into its body, causing it to get hotter and hotter. The more it cries, the stronger it becomes.
title: Molten Daughter

partnerSkill.name: Magma Tears
partnerSkill.description: Sometimes produces Flame Organ when assigned to Ranch.

name: Vanwyrm
lore: The melodies of a flute made from the exoskeleton of a Vanwyrm are said to cross whole mountain ranges. In ages past, such flutes were used to signal an attack.
title: Aerial Marauder

partnerSkill.name: Aerial Marauder
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden as a flying mount.

Increases damage player deals to enemy weak points while mounted.

name: Vanwyrm Cryst
lore: The melodies of a flute made from an exoskeleton of a Vanwyrm Cryst are said to cross whole mountains ranges. In ages past, such flutes where used to signal victory in battle.
title: Marauder of Frozen Skies

partnerSkill.name: Aerial Marauder
partnerSkill.description:
Can be ridden as a flying mount.

Increases daage player deals to enemy weak points while mounted.

name: Bushi
lore: Its body becomes a blade upon death, to be taken up by the next generation. if someone other then a Bushi wields this blade, the soul within torments them until they are driven mad.
title: Vagrant Warrior

partnerSkill.name: Brandish Blade
partnerSkill.description: When activated, attacks targeted enemy with a powerful Iaigiri.

name: Beakon
